{
  "texts": [
    "A token can represent ownership of a specific item (e.g., painting, land) and is not interchangeable with other tokens because it has unique (digital) properties encoded in the smart contract that creates it.",
    "For WoS, we also searched in Keywords Plus.",
    "It is a feature of WoS that returns the articles in results if the words or phrases in our search appear frequently in the titles of these articles' references, but not in the title of the article itself.",
    "By doing this, we also collected articles that have the potential to be relevant to our topic but did not have the keywords placed in the article.",
    "We cleaned the keywords of the papers before conducting the network analysis to eliminate the effects of the plural form, abbreviation, and spelling variation, etc."
  ]
}